06/02/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Office of the High Representative and the OSCE plan to draft a joint report assessing the media situation in BiH. Following a meeting Monday (February 5th), top international envoy Christian Schwarz-Schilling and OSCE Representative on Freedom of the Media Miklos Harasti issued a statement saying such a report would "help improve the climate in which this country's media operates". 
In other news, the Bosniak member of the BiH presidency, Haris Silajdzic, met with US Ambassador to BiH Douglas McElhaney to discuss the current situation in BiH and the region. They reiterated the importance of quickly forming new government institutions to resume reforms. (OHR Sources, Srna, BBC, OSCE website, PBS BiH - 05/02/07)
